It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. This is the last room in the house that has only been simply decorated.
Remove the ugly electric wall fireplace and grate. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Customize a closet.
We usually start with a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
Several dead birds were found, mummified, behind the flue :(
Prepare to welcome next week's plasterer
Satisfied with the small niche next to it
Install the new closet here (we haven't even started designing it 😈)
Haha, check what we found behind the radiator!
Remember to add the cute little ventilation openings to prevent moisture in the chimney
Install the chimney cover and chimney cap. The magpies nesting in the chimney should feel safer now 🪺
The plasterer is done. We'll lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork mats are laid, and we even made a dust collector accessory for the vacuum cleaner with toilet paper rolls to catch sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor is ready, so we can start laying it now. Let's have a cup of tea and rest for a while.
Well, today's progress was a bit slow because we had to cut around the doorframe to ensure a seamless transition with the hallway (which is also getting the floor laid), which was quite tricky. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me.
Finally done, but everything is a mess! And to top it off, the assembly instructions for the new bed are terrible. At least I can finally get a good night's sleep tonight!
There's still the hallway floor and baseboard to do. The renovator won't come for a month, so we're making do with just bare plasterboards in the room for now.
Tonight, do a simple DIY job by cutting part of the doorframe base with a tenon saw and chisel so the floor can fit perfectly underneath.
The cork mat for the hallway is also laid.
Yesterday we also laid the floor in the hallway! We got up at 5 this morning to go to Heathrow Airport to pick up package number one, then had a nap, and are finally ready to install the baseboard in the hallway. Let's wait for the glue to dry before filling any gaps.
